Regulated agents achieved optimal performance on Personality Needs Addressed (M = 2.00, SD = 0.00; 100\% YES ratings) compared to baseline's limited success (M = 0.17, SD = 0.42; 8.3\% YES ratings), yielding an exceptionally large effect size (Cliff's $\delta$ = 0.917, 95\% CI {[}0.83, 0.98{]}, p \textless{} 0.001). Cliff's delta of 0.917 indicates that regulated responses outperformed baseline in 91.7\% of pairwise comparisons, representing near-complete ordinal dominance. Figure 11 visualizes this selective enhancement pattern.

